<TEXT> nirālambam{ }anādhāram{ }anaupamyaṃ nirañjanam||</TEXT> 15:4
        <APP>\vd <LEM>°pamyaṃ</LEM> \msCa\msCb\msNa\msNc\Ed; °pamya \msNb</APP>
        <TR>Its pervasive, omnipresent, subtle, it exists dwelling in everything.
                 It is supportless, it is not contained in anything, it is unparalleled and spotless.</TR>

<TEXT> araṇistho yathā vahniḥ kāṣṭheṣu nopalabhyate|</TEXT>

<TEXT> tadvaj{ }jīvo na paśyeta śarīrastho 'pi sundari||</TEXT> 15:5
        <APP>\vc <LEM>jīvo na</LEM> \msCb\msNa\msNb\msNc; jīvon{ }na \msCa, jīvaṃ na \Ed</APP>
        <APP>\vd <LEM>'pi</LEM> \msCa\msCb\msNa\msNc\Ed; hi \msNb</APP>
        <TR>As fire [hidden] in fire-kindling sticks[?] is not perceivable in the wood,
                similarly the soul cannot be seen although it dwells in the body, O Sundarī.</TR>
        <NOTE>Note Łpaśyeta$ as a passive form.</NOTE>

<TEXT> dadhivac{ }ca yathā sarpir{ }dṛśyate na ca dṛśyate|</TEXT>

<TEXT> tadvaj{ }jīvaḥ śarīrastho dṛśyate na ca dṛśyate||</TEXT> 15:6
