<TEXT> vyāpī kathaṃ mahādeva sarvatrāvasthitaḥ katham||</TEXT> 15:7
        <APP>\vd <LEM>°sthitaḥ</LEM> \msCb\msNc\Ed; °sthitaṃ \msCa\msNa, °sthita \msNb</APP>
        <TR>Is it without any direct proof? Is there no way to directly see any proof [of its existence]?
                 How is it pervasive, O Mahādeva? How can it be omnipresent?</TR>
        % vyāpi ... sarvatra vasthitaḥ \Ed



<TEXT> maheśvara{ }uvāca|*</TEXT>
        <APP>\vo <LEM>maheśvara</LEM> \msCa\msCb\msNb\msNc; mahādeva \msNa, bhagavān \Ed</APP>
        <TR>Maheśvara spoke:</TR>

<TEXT> asaṃśayo mahādevi vyāpī sarvagataḥ śivaḥ|</TEXT>

<TEXT> dṛśyatendriyasaṃyogāj{ }jīvapratyayadarśanam||</TEXT> 15:8
        <APP>\vc <LEM>dṛśyate°</LEM> \msCb\msNa\msNb\msNc; dṛśyete° \msCa, dṛśyante \Ed</APP>
        <APP>\vd <LEM>°jīva°</LEM> \msCa\msCb\msNa\msNb\Ed; °jī° \msNc</APP>
        <TR>It is doubtlessly pervasive, omnipresent, it is Śiva.
                  It can be perceived through its contact with the senses. [That is] the direct perception of the evidence of
                        [the existence of] the soul.</TR>

<TEXT> yathākāśasthito vāyuḥ śabdasparśaguṇānvitaḥ|</TEXT>
        <APP>\vab <LEM>vāyuḥ śabda°</LEM> \msCb\msNa\msNb\msNc\Ed; vāyu<UNCL>śśa</UNCL>\lk\ \msCa</APP>
        <APP>\vb <LEM>°nvitaḥ</LEM> \msCa\msNa\msNb\msNc\Ed; °nvitam \msCb</APP>

